1. Project Management Commands

Command	Description
mvn clean	Cleans the project by deleting the target directory.
mvn compile	Compiles the source code of the project.
mvn test	Runs the tests using the test framework configured in the project.
mvn package	Packages the compiled code into a distributable format (e.g., JAR, WAR).
mvn install	Installs the package into the local repository for use as a dependency.
mvn deploy	Deploys the built package to a remote repository for sharing with other projects.



2. Dependency Management

Command	Description
mvn dependency:resolve	Resolves all dependencies for the project.
mvn dependency:tree	Displays the project's dependency tree.
mvn dependency:analyze	Analyzes the project's dependencies and suggests optimization (unused deps).
mvn dependency:purge-local-repository	Clears specific artifacts from the local repository.


3. Lifecycle Commands

Command	Description
mvn validate	Validates the project structure and the pom.xml file.
mvn verify	Verifies the project by running integration tests.
mvn site	Generates a project site with documentation and reports.


4. Plugins and Goals

Command	Description
mvn help:describe -Dplugin=<plugin>	Describes a specific plugin and its goals.
mvn exec:java -Dexec.mainClass=<main>	Executes the specified main class.
mvn install:install-file	Installs an external JAR to the local Maven repository.



5. Running Specific Profiles

Command	Description
mvn -P<profile>	Activates a specific profile defined in the pom.xml.
mvn package -P<profile>	Builds the package using a specific profile.


6. Skip Tests
Command	Description
mvn install -DskipTests	Skips test execution during the build process.
mvn install -Dmaven.test.skip=true	Skips test compilation and execution during the build process.


7. Debugging
Command	Description
mvn -X	Enables debug output for Maven commands.
mvn -e	Displays error details for failed commands.


8. Updating Dependencies
Command	Description
mvn dependency:resolve -U	Forces an update of dependencies from remote repositories.



9. Generate Archetypes
Command	Description
mvn archetype:generate	Creates a new project from a Maven archetype template.



10. Versioning
Command	Description
mvn versions:set -DnewVersion=<ver>	Updates the project's version in the pom.xml.
mvn versions:display-dependency-updates	Displays updates available for project dependencies.
Examples:
Clean and Build:
mvn clean install
Cleans the target directory and installs the package into the local repository.

Run a Java Class:
mvn exec:java -Dexec.mainClass="com.example.Main"
Runs the Main class in the project.

Skip Tests and Package:
mvn package -DskipTests

Packages the project without running tests.
